\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 88. C. balearica} Rodr.,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Fr.}{\b  16}: 237 (1869). Dwarf shrub. Stems c. 100 cm, much-branched. Leaves small; spring leaves undivided, linear; summer leaves pinnatisect, the terminal segment with 3 apical spines. Capitula solitary. Involucre c. 4 mm in diameter, ovoid; appendages spinose at apex, fimbriate-dentate. Florets yellow. Pappus 1/3-1/2 as long as achene. {\i Limestone rocks. • Islas Baleares.} Bl.
