\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. ARENARLAE (Hayek) Dostál. Stems herbaceous, the branches not spiny. Leaf-segments not rigid or spiny. Involucre usually ovoid; appendages usually spiny, not filiform and plumose-fimbriate at apex, the lower fimbriae confluent into a hyaline margin or forming auricles. Florets pink or purple, rarely yellow or lilac.
