\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 91. C. tenuiflora} DC., {\i Prodr.}{\b  6}: 584 (1838) ({\i C. ovina} sensu Bieb., non Pallas ex Willd.). Biennial. Stems 30-50 cm, erect, corymbosely branched. Leaves greenish, appressed-arachnoid-tomentose; lower 2-pinnatisect, the segments c. 1 mm wide, linear. Capitula in clusters. Involucre 7-8 × 3-4 mm, oblong-cylindrical; appendages dark brown, with white fimbriae, auriculate, with an apical spine 2-3 mm. Florets pink. Pappus about as long as achene. {\i Open hillsides. • From Bulgaria and Romania to Krym.} Bu Rm Rs (W, K).
